article.headline: Cleveland St. 81, Green Bay 64
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- J'Nathan Bullock scored a career-high 39 points to lead Cleveland State to an 81-64 win over Wisconsin-Green Bay on Monday night. Bullock made his first 11 field goal attempts and finished 13-of-14 shooting. The Vikings (16-10, 9-5 Horizon League) led by as many as 12 in the first half before the Phoenix scored the final nine points of the half to tie the game 37-37 at halftime. Cederic Jackson opened the second half with a jumper to spark a 29-8 run that gave the Vikings a 66-45 lead with 8:31 remaining. Breyohn Watson added 11 points for the Vikings, who have won two straight. Mike Schachtner lead the Phoenix (13-11, 7-7) with 13 points. Rahmon Fletcher and Ryan Tillema each scored 12 and Terry Evans added 11. The Phoenix have lost two in a row.
